That's perfectly fine! If a .gitignore file doesn't exist, you just need to create one.

The easiest way is to create a new file named exactly .gitignore in the root directory of your project (the same folder that contains your react and python folders).

Here is a good starter template for a project with both Python and React. You can copy and paste this into your new .gitignore file.

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
venv/
env/
*.env

# React
node_modules/
build/
dist/
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Common OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

.vscode/